FBIS3-35362 "drnes037_l_94009" FBIS-NES-94-037 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Feb 1994 ISRAEL Delegation To Head to Syria Via Cairo 27 Feb TA2402063494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 24 Feb 94 TA2402063494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] The Israeli Arab delegation headed by Knesset Member [MK] 'Abd-al-Wahhab Darawshah will be allowed to set out for Syria on 27 February via Cairo to deliver its condolences to President Hafiz al-Asad over the death of his son, Egyptian Ambassador Muhammad Basyuni informed MK Darawshah last night. He also told him that President al-Asad and the Syrian Government welcome the arrival of the Israeli Arab delegation. Our correspondent Qaysar Kabha reports that the delegation will consist of 50 members, including MK's Darawshah and Talib al-Sani'. The Egyptian Government will issue each delegate a one-time laissez-passer to enter Syria.
